{
  "texts": [
    "With the new improved vision system and two manipulators, the success rate for harvesting fruit was 86.0% and 55.8% for kiwifruit, with a cycle time of 2.78 s per unit (Williams et al. 2020).",
    "As shown in Fig. 6J, Mu et al. (2017) proposed a picking method with \"grab-pickslide\" and designed an end-effector with bionic fingers, information sensing, and machine vision for non-destructive kiwifruit picking.",
    "Tests showed a picking success rate of 90%, an average loss rate of 10%, and an average picking cycle time of 4 s. The device has great utility in achieving non-destructive fruit picking.",
    "As shown in Fig. 6K, He et al. (2022) proposed a two-arm cooperative method for mechanical picking of kiwifruit in orchards.",
    "The method consists of three steps: determining the picking position, collision detection, and a continuous picking cycle."
  ]
}